HEADWORD: Fishery
<hw>Fish"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Fisheries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The business
or practice of catching fish; fishing.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place for catching fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The right to take fish at a certain
place, or in particular waters.</def> <rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fishfly</ent>⟦br⟧
